# Cursor agent parallel workers & S1 EDR pacing

**Operator policy (2026-05-27):** Parallel background workers are **allowed** when safe and logical. The prior **max 1 subagent** ban is **retired**; incident history remains in [KNOWN_BUGS_AND_ISSUES.md](https://github.com/centexmsp/firewall-analysis/blob/main/docs/KNOWN_BUGS_AND_ISSUES.md) (2026-04-14 lockup).

## Parallel workers

- Cursor agents **MAY** spawn multiple background workers (**Task** / **explore** / **`run_in_background`**) for **independent** workstreams (e.g. system updates vs O.2 code vs docs).
- Prefer Cursor **Build in Parallel** / **`/multitask`** when lanes do not share files or branches ([pr-first-parallel-workflow-enforcement.mdc](pr-first-parallel-workflow-enforcement.mdc)).
- **Avoid duplicate work** on the same files/branches; coordinate via task list or explicit lane ownership.

## Safety (SentinelOne / EDR)

- **Incident context (2026-04-14):** Prompt bloat + **rapid** parallel tool bursts + many subagents contributed to S1 `keylogger.lua` false positives and lockups — see firewall-analysis **KNOWN_BUGS**.
- **Do not scan** `/opt/sentinelone/` or its logs without **explicit operator approval**.
- **Cap burst scanning** on one host if EDR alerts occur; fall back to **sequential, targeted** reads and **deliberate pacing** between heavy operations (mitigation, not a permanent agent count cap).
- **Prompt size awareness:** Avoid loading entire rule packs + full repo context in one turn when possible.

## MCP auth (unattended)

- **No proactive `mcp_auth`** in unattended/background runs unless the operator explicitly requests auth in that run ([agent-cloudflare-execution.mdc](agent-cloudflare-execution.mdc)).
- **Dedupe** `plugin-cloudflare-*` vs `user-cloudflare-*` MCP families; prefer already-authenticated servers.

